name: PHYE 5R
title: Aquatics: Basic Scuba Diving
description: Coeducational. Sections geared toward the successful completion of NAUI Scuba Diver Certification. The course is divided into three parts: lecture, pool lab, and open water experience. Four open water training dives are offered. Emphasis is on training for open water scuba diving, using the beach as a base of operation. Prerequisite(s): pass swimming skills tests and medical clearance. It is strongly recommended that students enroll in PHYE 5S.
